  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Starting at 6th level, when you successfully use Devil in the Details, you discover one of the following additional details, obtaining benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Weaknesses: </span></strong></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">one of the target’s flaws and for the next three attacks by you or your gregarious the target will be vulnerable to damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>Habits:</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">you can use your reaction to impose disadvantage to the target for an ability check or an attack roll in the next hour. You can use this reaction three times.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em><strong>Affinity:</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the target is charmed by you for a minute or until you or your gregarious acts in a hostile way.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Furthermore, you become able to break down language barriers, managing to understand a sentient creature and communicate effectively, regardless of whether they know its language.</span></p>",
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": ""
    },
    "source": "Historia Manuale pagina: 154",
